01:54.615 --> 01:55.673
"You people"?

01:55.816 --> 01:57.045
Mom, what's the matter?

01:57.184 --> 01:58.117
I'm fine.

01:58.251 --> 02:00.310
I'll fix you
a bite of something.

02:00.454 --> 02:02.115
Uh, they're just having
a little spat.

02:02.255 --> 02:03.484
We'll just ignore it.

02:03.624 --> 02:04.557
Oh, there's Dad.

02:04.691 --> 02:05.681
Oh!

02:08.595 --> 02:10.586
Good morning, Richard, Joanie.

02:13.033 --> 02:14.159
Good morning, Dad.

02:14.301 --> 02:15.632
I'll go to the kitchen.

02:15.769 --> 02:17.760
I'm told that's where I belong.

02:23.143 --> 02:25.635
Uh... nice day.

02:25.779 --> 02:26.905
Prove it.

02:30.083 --> 02:31.244
Dad, what's the matter?

02:31.385 --> 02:33.376
Nothing's the matter.

02:33.520 --> 02:34.885
Oh, listen to this.

02:35.022 --> 02:36.421
Your mother and I took this test

02:36.556 --> 02:38.684
in this magazine
and look what she said.

02:38.825 --> 02:40.725
"If you went out on a date
with your husband,

02:40.861 --> 02:41.919
"how would you rate him?

02:42.062 --> 02:44.429
<i>"'A,'</i> Wowsville;
'B,' a fun time;

02:44.564 --> 02:46.828
'C,' okay; and 'D,' a drag."

