14:07.013 --> 14:08.208
Howard, it isn't silly.

14:08.348 --> 14:09.838
Oh, this isn't working at all.

14:09.982 --> 14:11.848
It's your fault--
you're just not trying.

14:11.984 --> 14:14.476
I'm going to the room.

14:14.620 --> 14:17.089
I'm gonna tell your wife!

14:20.026 --> 14:22.017
She knows my wife?
She knows Gladys!

14:22.161 --> 14:24.220
I got to get out of here.

14:24.364 --> 14:27.026
Drinks for Cunningham!

14:33.005 --> 14:35.167
The stingrays.

14:36.743 --> 14:38.040
Fresh pineapples
are out of season,

14:38.177 --> 14:39.838
so we had to use the canned.

14:41.547 --> 14:44.175
Where is... Mrs. Cunningham?

14:44.317 --> 14:46.411
She went upstairs.

14:46.552 --> 14:49.214
Oh. You want I should take
the drink up to her?

14:49.355 --> 14:52.256
No. I think you
better leave it right here.

14:52.392 --> 14:56.056
Looks like it's gonna be
a long night.

15:00.233 --> 15:02.998
<i>II</i>

15:03.136 --> 15:06.106
No, no, no, no.
Listen, listen to me, will you?

15:06.239 --> 15:08.401
♪ Pennies in a stream ♪

15:08.541 --> 15:09.872
♪ Da, da, da... ♪

15:10.009 --> 15:12.478
Look, can't you send out
for the sheet music?

15:12.612 --> 15:16.412
If I could read music, you think
I'd be working a dump like this?

15:16.549 --> 15:18.881
Will you try it
one more time, huh?

15:19.018 --> 15:20.645
Right, folks? Huh?

15:20.787 --> 15:24.348
- No! -Nah!
-(groans)

15:26.492 --> 15:28.483
Please.

15:30.062 --> 15:32.292
Pretty please.

15:32.432 --> 15:35.265
I think it's coming back
to me now.

15:36.302 --> 15:40.933
♪ Pennies in a stream ♪

15:41.073 --> 15:45.135
♪ Falling leaves, a sycamore ♪

15:45.278 --> 15:48.270
♪ Moonlight in Vermont... ♪

15:48.414 --> 15:50.439
That's it! You got it!

15:50.583 --> 15:52.449
He's got it!

15:52.585 --> 15:54.576
<i>II</i>

16:02.829 --> 16:04.490
Hi.

16:08.668 --> 16:10.033
Hi.

16:10.169 --> 16:12.103
I'm looking for a man.

16:12.238 --> 16:14.104
(chuckles)

16:14.240 --> 16:15.969
I-I'm sorry.
I'm married.

16:16.108 --> 16:18.770
Oh. Well, actually,
I'm looking for a man

16:18.911 --> 16:20.811
who's supposed to meet me here.

16:20.947 --> 16:22.813
He was sitting at that table.

16:22.949 --> 16:26.351
Oh, uh, well,
he left a little while ago.

16:26.486 --> 16:28.181
It figures.

16:28.321 --> 16:30.483
Stood up again.

16:30.623 --> 16:33.320
And it's so hard
for me to meet men.

16:33.459 --> 16:35.791
I never know what to talk about,

16:35.928 --> 16:37.896
what to say.

16:38.030 --> 16:39.759
Want to buy me a drink?

16:41.934 --> 16:43.834
Jiminy Crickets.

16:43.970 --> 16:48.134
Oh, no, nothing fancy like that.

16:48.274 --> 16:50.265
Just a scotch.

16:51.911 --> 16:54.676
I'm footloose and fancy-free.

16:56.249 --> 16:58.775
My feet hurt
and I have children.

17:01.554 --> 17:04.546
Listen, you seem to be
a very nice young lady.

17:04.690 --> 17:07.057
Would you like
to do me a big favor?

17:07.193 --> 17:09.184
After the drink.

17:10.363 --> 17:12.194
No. No, no, no.

17:12.330 --> 17:14.698
Would you please dance with me?

17:14.834 --> 17:17.064
Oh. Sure, I'd love to.

17:17.203 --> 17:18.329
Oh.

17:18.471 --> 17:20.405
Oh. What's your favorite song?

17:20.540 --> 17:22.702
ALL:
"Moonlight in Vermont."

17:24.644 --> 17:26.635
