18:35.081 --> 18:36.276
♪ Dee da da dum ♪

18:36.415 --> 18:37.576
♪ Pa-dum pum! ♪

18:37.717 --> 18:38.946
Oh, Oh...

18:39.085 --> 18:41.019
We were caught in the dip.

18:42.521 --> 18:44.353
I'm glad you cut in,
uh, Mr. Cunningham,

18:44.490 --> 18:45.651
because I just remembered

18:45.791 --> 18:48.886
I have to take my brother Bruno
to his ballet class.

18:50.096 --> 18:52.929
Have a nice life together.
Oh, boy...

18:53.065 --> 18:54.499
-(door closes)
- Oh, Howard,

18:54.634 --> 18:56.659
I-I just wanted it to be
like our honeymoon.

18:56.802 --> 18:59.032
I wanted to dance
to "Moonlight in Vermont."

18:59.171 --> 19:00.639
Hmm. Somehow, Marion,

19:00.773 --> 19:02.468
I just can't recall you dancing

19:02.608 --> 19:04.406
with the bellhop 23 years ago.

19:05.978 --> 19:07.503
If I feel like dancing,
I'll dance.

19:07.647 --> 19:09.342
If I feel like being exciting,

19:09.482 --> 19:10.972
I'll just be exciting.

19:11.117 --> 19:13.950
No magazine test is
gonna tell me I'm average,

19:14.086 --> 19:15.679
nobody's gonna tell me
that I'm a

19:15.821 --> 19:16.913
I'm gonna sit here,

19:17.056 --> 19:19.991
I'm gonna eat my steak
and potatoes and peas...

19:21.694 --> 19:23.458
Average dinner.

19:24.497 --> 19:26.397
Oh... Howard,

19:26.532 --> 19:29.365
I guess I am just a

19:29.502 --> 19:31.368
I've always been average.

19:31.504 --> 19:33.666
So what?

19:33.806 --> 19:35.604
So you're an average

19:35.741 --> 19:38.142
and I'm an okay.

19:38.277 --> 19:40.769
I was an okay date
when you first met me

19:40.913 --> 19:42.904
and I'm an okay date now.

19:44.450 --> 19:47.442
We're both a couple
of "C"s, Marion.

19:49.488 --> 19:51.479
Mr. and Mrs. C.

19:52.658 --> 19:56.617
But I'll tell you something:

19:56.762 --> 19:58.856
If I have to be a "C,"

19:58.998 --> 20:01.865
I'm glad I have someone
as wonderful as you

20:02.001 --> 20:03.867
to be one with me.

20:04.003 --> 20:06.301
Oh... Howard.

20:10.176 --> 20:11.041
You know something?

20:11.177 --> 20:12.042
Hmm?

20:12.178 --> 20:13.668
We may be "C"s by ourselves,

20:13.813 --> 20:16.339
-but together, we're an
- Mmm.

20:16.482 --> 20:19.679
Othen/vise, why would
our children and Arthur

20:19.819 --> 20:21.514
go to all this trouble
to give us

20:21.654 --> 20:25.522
this wonderful,
wonderful second honeymoon?

20:25.658 --> 20:28.025
Marion...

20:28.160 --> 20:30.891
I could have not put it
in better words myself.

20:31.030 --> 20:32.498
And you're right, Howard.

20:32.631 --> 20:34.690
You can't relive the past.

20:34.834 --> 20:35.733
Mmm.

20:35.868 --> 20:37.233
You know something?

20:37.369 --> 20:39.394
What are a couple
of "A"s like us

20:39.538 --> 20:41.506
doing in a "D" hotel?

20:41.640 --> 20:43.540
Let's go home, huh?

20:47.113 --> 20:50.708
